1
00:00:08,020 --> 00:00:13,500
[1994 Huazhou Crematorium]

2
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:34,660
[Fang Qiang, Male]

3
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:19,940
[Producer Zhang Yimou]

4
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:49,780
[The First Shot]

5
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:52,620
[Episode 10]

6
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,400
Look, I got the timing just right.

7
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,320
- Uncle.
- Hurry up and eat breakfast.

8
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,400
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

9
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,640
You're a lifesaver.

10
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,120
I'm starving.

11
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,120
Sit down.

12
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,200
You've all worked hard.

13
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,880
Why are there only the three of you?
Where are the other two?

14
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,200
They're at the hospital.

15
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,320
At the hospital?

16
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,360
What happened? Who is injured?

17
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,120
Mr. Gu got hurt too?

18
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,480
He didn't make it.

19
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,240
What?

20
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,440
It's nothing.

21
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:17,040
Just a scrape, don't worry.

22
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,320
You little rascal.

23
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,720
A scrape and he's in the hospital?

24
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,960
And someone has to stay
to take care of him?

25
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,840
Speak clearly. How serious is it?

26
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,320
Really, it's nothing.

27
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,840
Just got hit by a brick.

28
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,000
Then got whacked.

29
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:27,880
And then got hit with a hammer.

30
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,560
Might even get hit
with a big iron ladle.

31
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,040
I'll hit you with a big iron ladle!

32
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,320
Speak properly. How are they really?

33
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,880
- It's nothing. Just eat.
- It's nothing.

34
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,360
- I'm exhausted.
- It's really nothing, Uncle.

35
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,320
You never take anything seriously.

36
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,800
Uncle, you're having noodles?

37
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,640
You arrived at the perfect time.

38
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,160
Xiong, you followed the smell,
didn't you?

39
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,040
Come, Xiong, come on.

40
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,840
Just the right time.

41
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,000
How did it go on your end?

42
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:46,960
Finished the interrogation.

43
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,360
What's the result?

44
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,360
The guy immediately ratted you out.

45
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,160
He said

46
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,440
you're a major pusher

47
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,760
with lots of goods,

48
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,560
offering a 10% discount.

49
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,000
He recognized him perfectly.

50
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:01,640
Hurry up and eat.

51
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,000
After you're done,
go back and finish the interrogation.

52
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,880
Take him away.

53
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,520
I guarantee to complete
this glorious task.

54
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,440
Anything else?

55
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,160
We've confirmed it.

56
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,640
This is what they call Lucifer.

57
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,640
Where did the goods come from?

58
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:15,480
I asked him for a long time,
but he couldn't tell.

59
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,880
He probably really doesn't know.

60
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,920
All he knows is
that it's in the Blue Aurora.

61
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,120
But

62
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:22,560
it only comes out when the big bosses

63
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:23,640
are hosting.

64
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,240
This guy doesn't have access to it.

65
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:26,440
Xiong, you hurry up.

66
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:28,360
- Eat and talk at the same time.
- Alright.

67
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,200
Or it'll all get soggy.

68
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,120
Alright.

69
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,560
This guy

70
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:34,640
is just a small-time pusher,
selling only Red Dragon.

71
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,560
At best, he's a middleman.

72
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,320
The goods come from above.

73
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,560
He only heard the name
Lucifer from others.

74
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,800
He gave me

75
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,520
accurate information about a warehouse.

76
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,360
Where is it?

77
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:46,640
Where's the map?

78
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,840
Sanlianer Factory?

79
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,800
Sanlianer?

80
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,160
You all know about it?

81
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,120
Yeah, that's the place
where they store Red Dragon.

82
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:58,160
Didn't we already discover it
during the taxi checks?

83
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,760
We've got people watching it.

84
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:06,080
But didn't you get
any useful information

85
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,320
after all that questioning?

86
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,160
The statements are all in here.

87
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,120
Finish eating first.

88
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,000
Afterward, take a good look at it.

89
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,400
If you have any questions,

90
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,720
I'll pull him out

91
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,160
and interrogate him again.

92
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,520
You're so slow, not doing anything
properly all day.

93
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,200
Honestly, though,

94
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,400
the food you guys have
in the special task force

95
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,560
is really tasty.

96
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,840
Uncle's cooking is excellent.

97
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,320
But you don't have to make that sound.

98
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:41,640
Eat more.

99
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,600
Eat more.

100
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,280
There's plenty.

101
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:47,480
Oh right, this guy gave me a name,

102
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,960
also something he heard
from the underworld.

103
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:51,200
He said this guy is the mastermind
behind the Lucifer deals.

104
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,400
What's his name?

105
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:56,760
It's a nickname.

106
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,200
They call him Mr. Ma.

107
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,560
Mr. Ma.

108
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,480
Oh, God.

109
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,400
So, what do you think we should do?

110
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,400
You're asking me what to do?

111
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,880
You got yourself into this mess,
so you figure it out.

112
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,520
Stop giving me trouble.

113
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:28,920
Welcome.

114
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:32,840
Madam.

115
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,280
Long time no see.

116
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,120
Welcome.

117
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,480
You handled things pretty quickly, huh?

118
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,600
Where did the fight happen?

119
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,160
Don't worry, Madam.

120
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:44,800
I'll make sure

121
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,320
to give you a perfect...

122
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,320
I'm asking you,

123
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,440
where did the fight happen?

124
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,200
Madam,

125
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,360
have some water.

126
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,240
Sorry for the lack of hospitality.

127
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,280
Where are they?

128
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,360
They're all outside.

129
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,560
Bring them in.

130
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:12,440
Madam,

131
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:13,800
this...

132
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:14,520
You guys.

133
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,560
Wang's glasses temple broke,

134
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,000
but the lenses are fine.

135
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,240
I found an identical one.

136
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,400
See if that's okay.

137
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,480
Line up. Stand properly.

138
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,960
These guys

139
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,920
were just recently transferred in.

140
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,440
They don't know the rules.

141
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,800
They really didn't mean to offend you.

142
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,800
Did they offend me?

143
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,720
They offended Wang.

144
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,120
If I had known

145
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,560
Wang was involved last night,

146
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,280
I would have handled it personally.

147
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,480
I wouldn't have let Wang
suffer like that, right?

148
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,640
Madam, this is just a small token
of my respect.

149
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:05,240
Do I need your money?

150
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,240
How about this?

151
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,040
I'll personally visit Wang

152
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,880
another day to apologize.

153
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:13,960
No need.

154
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,640
Wang is a clean man.

155
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:18,440
Don't drag him into this mess.

156
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,280
Madam, what do you want

157
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,160
if you were in that situation?

158
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,720
Who was the one
who started the fight last night?

159
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,520
Sen.

160
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:38,640
Erjin.

161
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,840
Were you blind?

162
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:43,280
Do you know who you've offended?

163
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,840
Boss, but they were the ones who...

164
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,920
Still talking?

165
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,680
Enough. Who are you putting on
this show for?

166
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:52,760
Madam,

167
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,760
this kid doesn't know any better.

168
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,440
I'll straighten him out for you.

169
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,680
Is that how you plan to handle it?

170
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,360
My Wang is lying
in the hospital right now.

171
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:06,160
His whole body is bruised.

172
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,520
He can hardly eat.

173
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,160
And this guy is standing here
without a scratch.

174
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:11,880
Do you think that's fair?

175
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:13,680
Madam,

176
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,400
what do you mean?

177
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,020
What the hell?

178
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,280
Did I tell you to do it?

179
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:11,880
Erjin.

180
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:13,560
Yes.

181
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,560
Wang doesn't know you,

182
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,440
but you know him, right?

183
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,280
Yes.

184
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:32,800
You know what kind of person he is,
don't you?

185
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,280
I've never seen anyone

186
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,640
more honest and decent than him.

187
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,160
No matter what happened last night,

188
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,800
he wasn't the one causing trouble.

189
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:41,760
That's right.

190
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:44,680
I know Wang is a clean guy.

191
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,480
If it wasn't for business,

192
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,400
he wouldn't have come
to a place like ours.

193
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,360
Good that you know.

194
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,640
You run a business, a club.

195
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,600
How you settle things is your business,

196
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,000
not mine.

197
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,040
But if you mess with my man,

198
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:03,480
I need an explanation, don't I?

199
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:05,720
Absolutely.

200
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,440
Madam,

201
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,040
please calm down.

202
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:12,600
Sen is

203
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,120
under my boss' protection.

204
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,520
He's just recently arrived
and doesn't know the rules.

205
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,480
That should be...

206
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,040
Are you trying

207
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,400
to intimidate me with Qin Yi?

208
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,200
No, Madam.

209
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,640
I didn't mean that.

210
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,800
When I married Wang,

211
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,880
I informed the underground.

212
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,720
Qin Yi knows that too.

213
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:44,680
Yes.

214
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,240
I've done him a favor

215
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:50,080
by not confronting him directly today.

216
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,680
If I really get angry,

217
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,480
he can forget
about running the Blue Aurora.

218
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,040
Don't think I don't know

219
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,760
what you did to Mu.

220
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:32,040
Is Jin Fei in her second year
of college this year?

221
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,640
Her grades are good, right?

222
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,160
You're managing the club
and the taxi fleet.

223
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,440
Are you able to handle it all?

224
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:44,920
It's going okay.

225
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,320
Well, Madam.

226
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,440
That...

227
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:50,680
That pearl necklace you gave to Fei,

228
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,320
she really treasures it.

229
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,960
She's reluctant to take it off.

230
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,000
That's good to hear.

231
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Let me tell you,

232
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,720
Jin Fei is a smart kid.

233
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,200
As long as she studies hard,

234
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,920
she'll definitely succeed in the future.

235
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:04,960
She mustn't get involved

236
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,080
in these messy matters.

237
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,160
Don't worry. I'll make sure
she stays away from such things.

238
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,200
Why are you still beating him?

239
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,280
That's enough.

240
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:29,880
Alright.

241
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:32,320
I really can't chat any longer today.

242
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,560
My Mao is still at home waiting for me

243
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:36,120
and I need to go home and cook for her.

244
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,120
I'm leaving.

245
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,200
Alright.

246
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:43,880
Madam, about the money...

247
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:44,880
I appreciate the gesture.

248
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,000
Keep it for medical expenses.

249
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:47,840
Thank you, Madam.

250
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:51,600
What are you looking at?

251
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,840
Hurry up and send him to the hospital.

252
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:03,840
Who's that woman?

253
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:05,200
She's ruthless.

254
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,520
Have you heard of Song the Slicer?

255
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,000
Is that her?

256
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:13,560
It's been years.

257
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:14,480
Is she still that formidable?

258
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,200
Alright.

259
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,640
Stop gossiping.

260
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:20,440
Bro.

261
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,880
I just heard her mention Fei.

262
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,120
She was threatening you
with those words.

263
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,520
Take me home first.

264
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:31,640
Later,

265
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,120
go to the hospital
and pick up Wang's medicine.

266
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,160
Okay.

267
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:40,280
[Mr. Ma?]

268
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,280
It seems now

269
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,840
that Qin Yi

270
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:46,440
is very likely
the Mr. Ma they mentioned.

271
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:51,080
That mild?

272
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,280
Why not Ma the Executioner?

273
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,720
If he were called Gedmis,

274
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,520
I'd be sure he's this old drug lord.

275
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,040
Don't digress.

276
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,480
We still need to investigate.

277
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:03,880
So far, we know

278
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:06,760
that Qin Yi's taxi company

279
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,280
is used for drug transportation.

280
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:10,560
The Sanlianer Factory is the warehouse.

281
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:13,040
Erjin, who manages the taxis,

282
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,040
happens to be his subordinate.

283
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:18,400
That's quite a solid chain of evidence.

284
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:22,640
Could the Lucifer we found yesterday

285
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:25,000
be the meth
from the White Building case?

286
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:25,920
I don't know.

287
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:28,280
